    <h1>Smaller but cosier festive mar&#xAD;kets</h1>
    <h2>Home decor, food, gifts &#x2013; get these and more at this year&#x2019;s festive mar&#xAD;kets, which may be smaller, but are cosier</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201127/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-27"><time>2020-11-27</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Amanda Chai aman&#xAD;dac@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>Festive mar­kets are trick­ling back just in time for Christ­mas.</p>
    <p>There will be no big atrium fairs with throng­ing crowds this year. In­stead, the mar­kets will be smaller, cosier af­fairs cu­rated and run by lo­cal ven­dors.</p>
    <p>Or you can shop from the com­fort of home – and re­spon­si­bly – at The Vir­tual Green Christ­mas Mar­ket.</p>
    <p>In line with safe dis­tanc­ing mea­sures, many of the mar­kets re­quire reg­is­tra­tion for en­try with lim­ited slots avail­able.</p>
    <p>The Straits Times scopes out the best mar­kets this festive pe­riod.</p>

